10:
Check out these guns! Don't they
look awesome?
13:
Definitely wouldn't want to be on the
wrong end of 'em.
17:
Hehe. Get ready for a harder, better,
faster Kannon!
21:
Is that gun really suited to your
current needs, though?
24:
Well, yeah? The stronger, the better,
right?
26:
Besides, my aim's all I got going for
me.
30:
Huh? You're gonna have to run that
by me again.
33:
You see any muscles on these
noodle arms, Nimbus? I was such a
bad melee fighter, the only party
requests I got were to be people's
pack mule.
36:
But that all changed when I found
my guns. Their strength is MY
strength, so you bet I'm gonna use
the best I can!
49:
All right, time to take these babies
on a test run!
59: It better not be, or we're all in trouble!
62:
I know that! Ohh, why isn't this
working?!
67:
What do I do? At this rate, we're
toast...
70:
Come on! You're supposed to make
smithereens outta these guys! Why
aren't you working?!
93:
Aww man. I really thought I hit it big
with those guns, but I couldn't get
them to work at all.
96:
They may be formidable weapons,
but they're not what you need right
now.
101:
Your strength is not defined by your
armaments alone.
102:
The battles you've fought have
given you hard-earned experience
that nothing can take away from
you.
104:
Believe in yourself, Kannon. You've
grown, and will continue to become
a better adventurer as time goes on.
108:
Yeah... I guess I have gotten
stronger, huh...
110:
I thought I was only able to hold my
own because of my weapons.
115:
But I've become a super top-tier
adventurer without even noticing it!
120: Wait. Let's not get carried away—
126:
Hehehe. Copperhead Kannon's
legend has grown even more epic!
You saw it here first!
130: I... guess she's grown? A little? Maybe?
